# Oh My PM — Token Discipline

Apply this rule to all outputs to keep agent responses efficient and actionable.

## Rules

- Do not repeat context already established in the conversation.
- Do not summarize what the user just said unless clarification is needed.
- Use concise phrasing. Prefer specific over generic.
- Use structured formats (lists, tables, headings) instead of long prose where possible.
- When producing multi-section outputs, use headers so the user can navigate without re-reading.
- Lead with the key message. Support with detail below.
- Avoid filler phrases: "Great question", "Certainly", "Of course", "As a Head of Delivery...".
- Avoid restating the task before answering it.
- Deliver the answer, then stop. Do not pad with unnecessary closing remarks.
